Revenue Recognition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Revenue recognition refers to when and how much revenues are shown in the
 I/S.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Under IFRS: when there is a probable flow of economic benefits to the company,
 with the risk and rewards transferred to the buyer and there is no involvment
 or control of the seller.
 Under US GAAP: earned, realized and reliably measured.
\end_layout

